Hope this helps!

snippet.textDisplay:
The metal boomerang, because of its increased mass, requires significantly more force, and a shallower angle of attack at the point of release...probably less than 45 degrees. Nate would basically have to throw it as hard as he can, with the proper angle. You might be able to improve it by putting large holes through each of the plates, making it lighter and easier to throw. You could put tape over the holes to maintain aerodynamic surface area and lift.

Something like the foam boomerang can be thrown perfectly vertically, with comparatively little effort, even by Calli...with the wooden ones largely being in the middle, regardless of size (to a point).

You should also look into making a launcher...both motorized, and one that's like a spear-thrower from ancient times.
